<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-49-0715 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Augsburg district heating system has been operating since 1954. Ithas a maximum thermal capacity of 110MW and the network is supplied withheat from the Franziskanergasse cogenerating (combined heat and power)station. The district heating grid is now being expanded. The objectivesof the expansion are to link up existing and new supply areas and toachieve optimal grid operation. This involves both the provision of newpipelines and the replacement of existing ones, the commissioning ofnew heating stations, and the possible commissioning of a refuse incinerationcogenerating plant. This article describes the expansion plans and howthe various options for system expansion were compared and evaluated.The construction programme for expansion is described.</TEXT></DOC>